        <DEPARTMENT dept_id="104673" dept_name="Hospitality/Health Care/BRE/Laundry-Laundry Room">
            <ITEM fqid="242202" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1722" question_code="029d" question_type="Data Capture" typeid="3">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[How many types of equipment were in the Hospitality/Health Care/BRE/Laundry-Laundry Room]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[The Covered Equipment section of the checklist must be accurate and updated whenever there is a change to the equipment or to the components of the equipment. The equipment that must be reported under Covered Equipment includes P&G dilution centers/dispensers, P&G wall pumps, P&G hand soap/sanitizer dispensers, P&G pan soakers, P&G carts, and/or P&G air fresheners. PGP MWW Program equipment is captured separately from this question. The equipment should have been initially captured during the 1st visit under the STAR system or when installed if after implementation of STAR. On subsequent visits the information from the previous visit will be pre-populated on the checklist. The FST must verify that this information is correct on every visit following the initial visit. Any changes to the equipment must be updated on each visit. This information needs to be kept current for record keeping, data reporting, and for use by the Call Center for telephone fixes and for assigning Reactive Service Calls.In stores where there are combined departments that share the dish sink, 3-lever, etc, (such as Deli/Bakery or Meat/Seafood) we would use the 'parent/child' concept where a Deli/Bakery would always be considered a Deli for purposes of the checklist; a Meat/Seafood would always be considered a Meat; etc. If there was a unique dept such as a Starbucks, the 'Other' department could be used. For example, if the Deli and Bakery were combined, you would have a Deli, but not a Bakery. Make a comment in the Deli Comment box, that this is a Deli/Bakery Combo department.Document the covered equipment by entering the number of equipment types in the department or area selected. The number of equipment lines that open up is dependent upon the number you enter. Equipment lines will show up in the department dropdown with 'Equipment #' displayed?. Enter hand soap and/or hand sanitizer dispensers as 1 per dept or area, even if there is more than one in the dept or area. All dilution centers other than hand soap and hand sanitizer dispensers should be entered 1 at a time unless there are identical equipment (same equipment, loop, eductor, and tip/ULD) in the same department. If there are identical pieces of any of the equipment in the department you will get a follow-up question to enter the number of identical pieces.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
        </DEPARTMENT>
