            <ITEM fqid="242096" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1507" question_code="028u" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Were Safeguard Hand Soap/Hand Sanitizer Dispensers working?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Visually inspect dispenser and operate pushbar. Repair dispensers as needed. Replace dispensers if needed and available in car stock. If replacement is needed but not in car stock, advise store to order. Some locations have stainless steel dispensers and they should not be removed without permission. They may be compatible with dispensing our product. If compatible and working properly technician should enter details on Comments box. Drip trays are required for most dispensers. FSTs should be familiar with the NSO drip tray policy. As many 'No' Suggested Comments as apply may be selected.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242097" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2008" question_code="015g3a" question_type="Multiple Choice" typeid="2">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[CQ Quat Sanitizer reading UPON ARRIVAL]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Take this reading before starting any work on the sanitizer dilution equipment. Run fresh Sanitizer into a small clean container. Water needs to be room temp - approx. 70 degrees. Let foam settle and disappear. Test solution for 10 seconds, holding test strip perfectly still. Sanitizer should test at 200 ppm. Broad Range Quat actually performs properly from 150 - 400 ppm but is not always accepted by local Health Department. Enter the reading.]]></POLICY>
                <ANSWER_CHOICES>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm067" fqacid="302972" text="No Test Strips Available"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm018" fqacid="302987" text="150 PPM"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm065" fqacid="302992" text="400 PPM"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm064" fqacid="303044" text="300 PPM"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm068" fqacid="303061" text="Test Strips expired"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOac322" fqacid="303127" text="No Sanitizer of any type/brand available"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOac401" fqacid="303183" text="N/A-CQ Quat not required"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm063" fqacid="303216" text="0 PPM"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm066" fqacid="303365" text="Above 400 PPM"/>
                </ANSWER_CHOICES>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242099" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1506" question_code="028v" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Were hand sinks working, equipped and with signs?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[The hand wash sinks must be able to dispense hot and cold water @ a minimum of 100ÂºF (110ÂºF in CA) and must be in good working condition. The hand wash station must also be free of any obstructions, such as racks, mop buckets, equipment, trash, etc.The hand wash station must be supplied with approved hand soap and either paper towels or a heated air dryer. Under NO circumstances should the more durable hard plastic 'Employees must wash hands before returning to work' signs and 'Hand wash only' or other customer provided signs be removed without asking the PIC. Some customers use their own hand wash signs/stickers at hand wash sinks. Techs shouls be knowledgeable of which of their customers use their own in place of P&G hand wash stickers. Select 'Yes' if you can answer all 3 elements of the question in the positive. As many 'No' Suggested Comments as apply may be selected.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242105" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1931" question_code="090" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Did you review the task area opportunities with the Person In Charge?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[If you answer 'Yes', no comment is required. If you answer 'No', you will need to enter a comment. Select the Suggested Comment or enter other reason in the text box.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
