            <ITEM fqid="242110" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2311" question_code="028y3" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was DCT Power Force II Oven Cleaner on hand?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Evaluate the products ensuring that they are available and used according to P&G's specifications. Do a thorough search for the products and ask the PIC if the products could be stored in another area if you cannot find. If not please educate PIC. If applicable, advise that dispensing the wrong product or a competitor?s product through the equipment is not permissible.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242111" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2095" question_code="015c" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Did FIT Veggie Wash reach the targeted dilution concentration range UPON ARRIVAL?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Range should be 60-85 using MicroEssentials Hydrion test strips. If within range select the appropriate 'Yes' comment. If answering 'No' select the appropriate 'No' pre-typed comment.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242112" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1950" question_code="015f" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was an automated dilution control center being used in the Custodial Closet?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[This question applies to PGP equipment only. A custodial closet or a mop sink could be in an enclosed area or in an open area. Must have a dilution center to be considered automated.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242114" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1579" question_code="028v3" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was this a Baskin or a Dunkin Baskin Combo store?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Select 'Yes' if this is specifically intended for a Baskin or Dunkin Combo location. A 'Yes' answer will prompt the correct Baskin/Combo specific questions to your work order.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242117" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2352" question_code="015g4" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Did CQ Quat Sanitizer test at 200 PPM UPON ARRIVAL at the additional automated dilution control centers?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[If the CQ Quat test does not reach 200 PPM, ensure that the result is within range of the US Health Department requirements of 150 PPM ? 400 PPM and note the final test result in the comment. Describe in the comment any suspected root causes preventing a test result of 200 PPM. Tech should train PIC and others on sanitizer testing as needed. Answer the 'Yes' or 'No' based on the initial test; not on a test following corrective action. As many 'No' Suggested Comments as apply may be selected. Enter any additional details in the Comment box. 'No' answers will bring up additional questions.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242120" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2047" question_code="007l" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Did the location have sufficient chemical inventory?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[There must be enoughproduct for each dilution center/dispenser. Sufficient inventory for purposesof this question is 1 bottle/jug attached to the dilution center/dispenser. Forhand soap and hand sanitizer there should be at least some product that can beextracted from the dispensers. For MWW products there should also be at least 1bottle/jug in storage. Tech must be aware of what products are required for thecustomer to answer this question correctly. A 'Yes' answer means that allrequired products have a sufficient inventory as described above. If any of therequired products do not meet the definition of sufficient inventory answer'No' and select all of the applicable suggested comments (picks).]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242122" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2094" question_code="015c2" question_type="Data Capture" typeid="3">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Fit Veggie Wash dilution concentration reading AFTER ACTION TAKEN]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Test the dilution concentration again using MicroEssentials Hydrion test strips. Enter the reading. Range should be 60-85 using MicroEssentials Hydrion test strips.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242126" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2045" question_code="028p2" question_type="Multiple Choice" typeid="2">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Work performed on the Hydro Mobile Cart or Lafferty 3 Lever Hose System Cart]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[ComprehensivePM vs Operational PMs (NOTE:?ComprehensivePM? and ?Operational PM? are internal TSO terms and not to be used with thecustomers. The only term used with the customer and the only term appearing oncustomer reports will be ?PM?. For the fields ?Work performed on the equipmentat the 3 comp sink, mop sink, etc?, the pick ?3-comp, mop sink, etc PMcompleted? applies to both Comprehensive and Operational PMs.)1. For Total Kitchen customers, complete the entire MWW PM part of thechecklist on every PM. For the PGP non-MWW equipment in Total Kitchenlocations, a Comprehensive PM will be performed once a year and the other PMvisits during the year will get an Operational PM. 2. For customers receiving one annual PM or RE PM, (restaurants,C-stores, etc), a Comprehensive PM will be required on the one annual visit. 3. For non-MWW customers receiving more than one PM annually, only oneof the PMs will be a Comprehensive PM and the others will be OperationalPMs. (See the Service Entitlements Workbook on Box.net)Comprehensive PM Requirements: Check and test all component parts (inside andoutside) of the dilution center, wall pumps, or dispensers to make sure they arefunctioning properly. Check for proper mounting. Visually inspect thatcorrect mating caps or foot valve assembly parts are in place and in goodcondition. Replace any rusting screws. Clean all PGP equipment inside andout.  Make any installation adjustments needed or detail why theycould not be done. Check the condition of racks and that they are securelyattached. All product supply wall racks must be mounted below eye level.Preferably, racks should not be mounted below the water supply or the dilutioncenter. FSTs should be knowledgeable of their assigned customers? preferencesfor mounting racks above or below the 3-comp sink. Fill spray bottles if low orempty. The Comprehensive PM includes annual replacement of the following partsregardless of condition: Metering tips/ULDs (refer to metering tipcharts), gray air gap eductors for Comet w/Bleach and Comet DisinfectingCleaner with Bleach, hose barbs that connect the supply tubing to the Cometeductors, inlet water strainers, Select equipment knobs and suction inlet onall Select equipment. On the checklist, select all items from the list thatapply. If unable to replace any of these parts or if any of these parts hadalready been replaced during the current CY, please explain in Comments. Operational PM Requirements:  Operational PMs of the non-MWW PGP equipment includestesting and repairing the equipment as needed to ensure proper operation anddilution. Testing all sanitizer levels will be part of each Operational PM. Italso includes cleaning the equipment on every visit. If needed, the tech willreplace stickers, wall charts, and any parts required to keep the equipmentoperational.]]></POLICY>
                <ANSWER_CHOICES>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOpm053" fqacid="302909" text="Hydro Mobile Cart/Lafferty 3 Lever Hose System Cart PM completed "/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOac477" fqacid="302954" text="Backflow repaired/replaced"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOac189" fqacid="303136" text="Dilution Center repair completed"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOac192" fqacid="303215" text="Water leak repaired"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOac190" fqacid="303359" text="Parts/equipment replaced"/>
                    <ANSWER_CHOICE code="TSOac191" fqacid="303377" text="Product flow repaired"/>
                </ANSWER_CHOICES>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242127" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1384" question_code="028y1" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was the Crisis Management Center available and mounted?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[The Crisis Management Center is a wall mounted rack that should be located in the back of the restaurant, with access at all times to all crew members. This has valuable information for the restaurant to use during various emergency situations such as flooding, power outage, sick guest, fire. Please locate this resource. If selecting 'No', select the appropriate Suggested Comment. If not available, ask the PIC to contact DMI Print to order it. They can find this information by going to the Dunkin Brands Online University, then to the Dunkin Donuts Restaurant Manager Knowledge Center. At this point the PIC should click onto the OPS Source link and access the resource section for the DMI contact.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242138" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1615" question_code="061" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Were the current Safety Data Sheets (SDS) available?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Check to see if current Safety Data Sheets (SDS) are available for all PGP products used by the customer including products that may be out of stock on the day of the PM. Select ?Yes? if SDS are available for all products used by the customer. If one or more Safety Data Sheets are missing, select 'NO' and the pre-typed comment. The preferred method for the customer to obtain a missing SDS is via pgpro.com. Only if internet access is not available should the customer be advised to call the P&G Customer Contact Center at 800-332-7787.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242139" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2053" question_code="062" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was the current Procedure Manual available?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Check to see if current Procedures Manual is available. Select ?Yes? if the current Procedures Manual is available.  If the manual is missing, advise the customer to contact the Call Center for one and select 'NO' and the pre-typed comment.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242140" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="2312" question_code="028y5" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Did we complete connection conversion to PG set-up?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[If there is a Blodgett Grilled Chicken Oven in the location and DCT Powerforce II Oven Cleaner is on hand, complete the conversion IAW the instructions on Box.net at NSO Field Reference Files>Customers>YUM! Brands>YUM! Brands General Information>KFC. If there is a Blodgett oven and Powerforce II available and you did not do the conversion, answer ?No? and enter a comment explaining why the conversion was not done. If DCT Powerforce II Oven Cleaner has been in use the supply tubing and mating cap for this product must be replaced annually.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242141" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1530" question_code="009m" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Were test strips and test strip box available and in use?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[The sanitizer test strip boxes should be mounted near the 3-comp sink IAW the Cleaners Equipment Installation Guide and contain test strips. Preferred location is above sanitizer drip board so that it is not directly above water. Please remind stores that test strips come in a small envelope in each case of sanitizer but often fall to bottom of case.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
