            <ITEM fqid="242153" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1777" question_code="075" question_type="Data Capture" typeid="3">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Work order notes/work performed summary]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[On the PM, INS, and RE WO/checklists, the purpose of this field is to summarize the work purformed on this visit in a few words. Bring out what stood out about this visit. If nothing stood out, say that, too, such as 'Executed PM and all went well'.The work performed box should be used to record any information that is outside of the normal scope of the work order. Special request, special training topics, names of PIC or others that you spoke with about ?out of scope? items, etc. Information regarding scheduling attempts, confirmations or other ?key? scheduling information can also be included (in detail) here. The information recorded here allows P&G and customer management to single out those issues that need further investigation. Finally, if you are cancelling a work order ? this is the place to record the detailed reason behind the cancellation. You must include the date of the cancellation and your name also with this information.On the RSC checklist, the information entered should be a summary of what you did on this visit. On this checklist there is no other description area for all the work the FST performs on the visit. This information is read by P&G and customer management. Information entered should be clear, detailed, and professional.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242154" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1386" question_code="028w" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was the dipper well clean and flowing with bubbles?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Dipper well water flow must be operational with strong enough force to create air bubbles in the dipper well water; the water flow is required to be strong enough to adequately rinse residual ingredients, including allergens, between scoop & spade use. If 'No' is selected, choose the appropriate Suggested Comment or Comments.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
