        <DEPARTMENT dept_id="104683" dept_name="PM Standard-Qualifying Questions">
            <ITEM fqid="242223" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1778" question_code="002" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was this location PG chemical compliant (using 1 or more P&G products through a dilution center/dispenser/RTU)?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Customer locations should be using 1 or more P&G products that are intended for dilution thru the location?s dilution centers and dispensers and/or P&G RTU products, packets or products dispensed thru dilution jugs. Select ?Yes? if the location is using 1 or more PGP products of any type. If not using any P&G products, select the applicable ?No? Suggested Comment and send an e-mail with details to the Team Leader. If the location is not using at least one P&G product, the PM should be terminated and the Manager or PIC advised to order P&G products. Dunkin is the exception. Please select 'Yes' even if the Dunkin Brands location does not have any P&G products and select the pre-typed comment 'NA-Dunkin PM'. We are required to complete the PM at every Dunkin Brands location.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242231" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1570" question_code="001" question_type="True/False" typeid="1">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[Was the Location Open?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Assess the open status of the facility. In the event of a remodel, attempt to discuss next steps with PIC to ensure that the program is reinstalled properly. Provide PIC with Customer Service 1-800#. Temporary closure may include Boil Water Orders, Road Construction, Power Outage or other challenges that the facility may be faced with. Temporary closures will require a reschedule within approximately 30 days after being notified that the facility has reopened. If access is denied to any area of the facility technician must include detailed notes regarding the situation including the name of the person denying access, time of day, and other pertinent comments. If you select any of the 'No' picks, make a Comment and close the WO without answering any other questions. Suggested Comments with 'COMMENT' at the end require detailed Comments.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
        </DEPARTMENT>
        <DEPARTMENT dept_id="104684" dept_name="CML-Dish Sink">
            <ITEM fqid="242123" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1720" question_code="029f" question_type="Data Capture" typeid="3">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[How many types of equipment were in the CML-Dish Sink?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[The Covered Equipment section of the checklist must be accurate and updated whenever there is a change to the equipment or to the components of the equipment. The equipment that must be reported under Covered Equipment includes P&G dilution centers/dispensers, P&G wall pumps, P&G hand soap/sanitizer dispensers, P&G pan soakers, P&G carts, and/or P&G air fresheners. PGP MWW Program equipment is captured separately from this question. The equipment should have been initially captured during the 1st visit under the STAR system or when installed if after implementation of STAR. On subsequent visits the information from the previous visit will be pre-populated on the checklist. The FST must verify that this information is correct on every visit following the initial visit. Any changes to the equipment must be updated on each visit. This information needs to be kept current for record keeping, data reporting, and for use by the Call Center for telephone fixes and for assigning Reactive Service Calls.In stores where there are combined departments that share the dish sink, 3-lever, etc, (such as Deli/Bakery or Meat/Seafood) we would use the 'parent/child' concept where a Deli/Bakery would always be considered a Deli for purposes of the checklist; a Meat/Seafood would always be considered a Meat; etc. If there was a unique dept such as a Starbucks, the 'Other' department could be used. For example, if the Deli and Bakery were combined, you would have a Deli, but not a Bakery. Make a comment in the Deli Comment box, that this is a Deli/Bakery Combo department.Document the covered equipment by entering the number of equipment types in the department or area selected. The number of equipment lines that open up is dependent upon the number you enter. Equipment lines will show up in the department dropdown with 'Equipment #' displayed?. Enter hand soap and/or hand sanitizer dispensers as 1 per dept or area, even if there is more than one in the dept or area. All dilution centers other than hand soap and hand sanitizer dispensers should be entered 1 at a time unless there are identical equipment (same equipment, loop, eductor, and tip/ULD) in the same department. If there are identical pieces of any of the equipment in the department you will get a follow-up question to enter the number of identical pieces.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
            <ITEM fqid="242145" is_admin_question="0" is_focus_question="0" is_info_only="0" qid="1900" question_code="047b" question_type="Data Capture" typeid="3">
                <QUESTION><![CDATA[How many MWW machines were in the CML-Dish Sink?]]></QUESTION>
                <POLICY><![CDATA[Enter the number of MWW machines on the PGP MWW program. Be sure to count every MWW machine that is on the PGP MWW program. One or two machines are common, but some locations have more. Verify with the MOD/PIC that you have included all machines on PGP MWW program.]]></POLICY>
                <QUESTION_TAGS/>
            </ITEM>
        </DEPARTMENT>
